dc_description_s: AMS 1. North Decimal Degree 22.450000. South Decimal Degree 22.400000. East Decimal Degree 120.583333. West Decimal Degree 120.533333. Alternate title: Kato. In upper left margin: Formosa city plans 1:10,000. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. Compiled in 1944 from aerial photography dated November 1943 and March 1944 by photo-planimetric method and by reference to Formosa 1:50,000, A.M.S. Sheet 2214 III, 1944. Additional information from intelligence data. Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. With a glossary. Name has been changed to Lai-chia.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1944.
